<TITLE> PM concerned for groundwater depletion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has said that the government has adopted a plan to use more surface water in Dhaka as the water table is being depleted by an escalating population. During the prime minister's question time, she said the level of underground water is falling 2-3 metres every year. The government is aware of the matter, she said, replying to a query by Comilla MP Nasimul Alam Chowdhury. The situation might cause disasters like subsidence, Hasina said. bd
